HEADWORD: Lockjaw
<hw>Lock"jaw`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A
contraction of the muscles of the jaw by which its motion is suspended;
a variety of tetanus; trismus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

